news.title: Brilloca to acquire building products manufacturing business of HSIL for Rs 630 crore
news.para: ​​Currently engaged in marketing and distribution of building products such as sanitaryware, faucets, plastic pipes and fittings, Brilloca said after the acquisition it will be backward integrated and have better control over the entire value chain, from manufacturing to after-sales.

news.title: Varanasi civic body freezes bank accounts of house tax debtors
news.para: VMCs zonal officer (trans-Varuna) PK Dwivedi said that despite issuance of demand notice and warrant many big debtors did not realized the need to clear their house tax.

news.title: Mumbai: In redevelopment market, future of heritage houses on fragile ground
news.para: Over the past two decades, several heritage properties have been redeveloped with their heritage facade retained and a tower built behind it.

news.title: Bengaluru: Govinda Reddy Layout citizens are in despair
news.para: At Govinda Reddy Layout (Ward no 50), near Hosa Road, local residents allege that the storm-water drains have been constructed at a higher level than their houses, which was not helping with the flooding at all.

news.title: Chandigarh civic body all set to notify construction & demolition waste policy
news.para: Since the C&D waste policy is a new one, it will be notified by the Punjab governor and UT administrator in consultation with senior officials of the Chandigarh administration.

news.title: Dip into e-wallet to pay property tax in Kolkata
news.para: ​​This apart, the KMC brass will also offer a citizen to apply for mutation of his/her properties online and upload the property-related documents for verification by the civic officials before issuing a mutation certificate.

news.title: Jharkhand: Brick kilns want exemption from green norms
news.para: ​​The brick manufacturers, who are ready to opt for cleaner technology, are sceptical that stringent laws may push the small and medium business owners out of the trade.

news.title: For lack of building use nod, 24 units sealed in Ahmedabad
news.para: On Bopal BRTS Road, the AMC sealed 14 residential units in Baleshwar Society and a unit in Anveshan Society. Apart from that, along Fathehwadi canal road, eight units were sealed. In all, AMC sealed 16 commercial and eight residential units.

news.title: Mohali: Dara Buildtech and Developer booked for fraud
news.para: The resident of Sector 36 alleged Rahul Mehra alias Rahul Dara, MD, and others of Dara Buildtech and Developer launched a housing scheme for allotment of 1BHK flats at Mohali with a project named “Dara Kingdom”.

news.title: UK's Planet Holdings invests in Pune realty project
news.para: Planet Holdings and Kolte-Patil Developers have invested ₹60 crore and ₹15 crore, respectively, in compulsorily convertible preference shares (CCPS) of Snowflower Properties.

news.title: Mumbai company set to get nod to raze Supertech twin towers as SC watches
news.para: The Noida Authority went by the technical examination report prepared by experts from the Central Building Research Institute in Roorkee before giving the final approval, senior officials said.

news.title: China new home prices fall at slower pace in December 2021
news.para: Average new home prices in China's 70 major cities declined 0.2% in December from a month earlier, slower than a 0.3% drop in November, according to Reuters calculations from data released by the National Bureau of Statistics (NBS).

news.title: Protests in New York as eviction moratorium due to end
news.para: The moratorium, granted in spring of 2020 by then governor Andrew Cuomo, has been regularly extended since then, but current governor Kathy Hochul has declined to do so after it is due to expire on Saturday.

news.title: Explain regularisation of illegal residential colonies on pasture land: HC to Rajasthan govt
news.para: ​​In its petition, the Shri Rajasthan Gau Seva Samiti stated the state government had introduced a policy on December 27 last year to regularise encroachments on the pasture land or gochar, which are over 35 years old.

news.title: Mumbai: ED attaches Omkar group's flats at Worli worth Rs 330 crore
news.para: Earlier, the ED had arrested Babulal Varma and Kamal Kishor, managing director and chairman of the Omkar group, respectively, in the case along with Sachin Joshi, promoter of J M Joshi group.
